{"Title": "Conducting Experiments in Public Management Research: A Practical Guide", "Year": 2015, "Source": "Int. Public Manage. J.", "Volume": "18", "Issue": 2, "Art.No": null, "PageStart": 323, "PageEnd": 342, "CitedBy": 23, "DOI": "10.1080/10967494.2015.1024905", "Link": "https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?partnerID=HzOxMe3b&scp=84931440609&origin=inward", "Abstract": "\u00a9 2015, Taylor & Francis Group, LLC.ABSTRACT: This article provides advice on how to meet the practical challenges of experimental methods within public management research. We focus on lab, field, and survey experiments. For each of these types of experiments we outline the major challenges and limitations encountered when implementing experiments in practice and discuss tips, standards, and common mistakes to avoid. The article is multi-authored in order to benefit from the practical lessons drawn by a number of experimental researchers.", "AuthorKeywords": null, "IndexKeywords": null, "DocumentType": "Journal", "PublicationStage": null, "OpenAccess": 2, "EID": "2-s2.0-84931440609", "SubjectAreas": [["Business and International Management", "BUSI", "1403"], ["Public Administration", "SOCI", "3321"]], "AuthorData": {"35309171200": {"Name": "Baekgaard M.", "AuthorID": "35309171200", "AffiliationID": "60029616", "AffiliationName": "Aarhus University"}, "6603416225": {"Name": "Blom-Hansen J.", "AuthorID": "6603416225", "AffiliationID": "60029616", "AffiliationName": "Aarhus University"}, "36684065100": {"Name": "Jakobsen M.", "AuthorID": "36684065100", "AffiliationID": "60029616", "AffiliationName": "Aarhus University"}, "55990808300": {"Name": "Serritzlew S.", "AuthorID": "55990808300", "AffiliationID": "60029616", "AffiliationName": "Aarhus University"}, "56689411500": {"Name": "Thomsen M.K.", "AuthorID": "56689411500", "AffiliationID": "60029616", "AffiliationName": "Aarhus University"}, "56689675800": {"Name": "Baethge C.", "AuthorID": "56689675800", "AffiliationID": "60014151", "Affi